{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780204759559,"sessionID":"ses_1838ab6e9ffeatBu2yU5LNM9VH","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_function_mwmr2n5icn9l_2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":1,\"model\":\"hs\",\"newInfoRatio\":0.6,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"iter1\",\"findings\":5}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-hs-i1-01\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"file\":\".opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs\",\"line\":59,\"issue\":\"parseIntentSignals entry regex [^}]* cannot parse nested braces in intent-signal values. For KEY: {weight:1, keywords:[a], meta:{priority:high}}, [^}]* stops at first } inside the meta object, truncating keywords before kwMatch can find them.\",\"fix\":\"Replace [^}]* with a brace-depth-tracking parser or nested-regex to handle one level of nesting, or switch to Function('return{'+body+'}') with try/catch fallback.\"}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-hs-i1-02\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"file\":\".opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs\",\"line\":65,\"issue\":\"kwMatch regex [^\\\\]]* cannot parse nested brackets in keyword arrays. For keywords: [a, [b, c]], [^\\\\]]* stops at inner ], causing quotedStrings to extract only 'a' and 'b', silently dropping 'c'.\",\"fix\":\"Use a bracket-depth-tracking parser for the keywords array, or restrict SKILL.md format to flat keyword arrays only and document the constraint.\"}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-hs-i1-03\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"file\":\".opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs\",\"line\":31,\"issue\":\"extractDictBody indexOf('{') finds the first { after name=, but does not skip string literals. If DEFAULT_RESOURCE path contains a brace (e.g., style/{id}.css), depth tracking starts at the wrong position, producing null or a wrong substring.\",\"fix\":\"Track whether characters fall inside a quoted string; skip string content when searching for structural braces, or normalize/escape brace sequences in paths before lookup.\"}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-hs-i1-04\",\"severity\":\"P2\",\"file\":\".opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/d5-connectivity.cjs\",\"line\":47,\"issue\":\"Early-return path (missing SKILL.md) sets score:0. Normal path for same condition would produce score:60 (one P0=40 penalty). gateFailed:true masks the inconsistency but returned score is mathematically inconsistent with the penalty formula, confusing for debugging.\",\"fix\":\"Harmonize early-return score with the penalty formula (score:60) or refactor so both code paths share the same scoring logic.\"}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-hs-i1-05\",\"severity\":\"P2\",\"file\":\".opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/score-skill-benchmark.cjs\",\"line\":49,\"issue\":\"D1-intra uses hard-coded 0.4/0.6 weights for intentRecall/resourceRecall with no justification comment. Comment at line 16 says D1=25 (inter12+intra13) but does not explain how 0.4/0.6 maps to the 13-point intra allocation.\",\"fix\":\"Add a comment explaining the 0.4/0.6 rationale and confirming it sums correctly to the 13-point D1-intra weight.\"}\n","filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/006-deep-review/review/hs/deltas/iter-001.jsonl"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/006-deep-review/review/hs/deltas/iter-001.jsonl","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/006-deep-review/review/hs/deltas/iter-001.jsonl","time":{"start":1780204759537,"end":1780204759557}},"id":"prt_e7c78bd45001YAmU1CzTW4BfR8","sessionI